<taxonomicName id="13914D5BFFC1BB572FF32FD10BC0FC47" authority="Giordani-Soika, 1950" authorityName="Giordani-Soika" authorityYear="1950" box="[193,714,942,969]" class="Malacostraca" family="Calliopiidae" genus="Apherusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chiereghinii">
<emphasis id="E6E5EACAFFC1BB572FF32FD108CEFC46" bold="true" box="[193,452,942,969]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="390">Apherusa chiereghinii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B0004B29FFC1BB572EF92FD10BC0FC47" author="Giordani-Soika, A." box="[459,714,942,968]" pageId="17" pageNumber="390" pagination="165 - 212" refId="ref20080" refString="Giordani-Soika, A. (1950) Gli Anfipodi gammarini della laguna di Venezia. Archivio di Oceanograja e Limnologia, 6 (2 - 3), 165 - 212." type="journal article" year="1950">Giordani-Soika, 1950</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9C8B6553FFC1BB572FA52F8908E3FBBA" pageId="17" pageNumber="390" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="D42E36D8FFC1BB572FA52F8908E3FBBA" blockId="17.[151,1437,1014,1438]" pageId="17" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis id="E6E5EACAFFC1BB572FA52F890887FB9F" bold="true" box="[151,397,1014,1040]" pageId="17" pageNumber="390">Materials examined.</emphasis>
25 individuals; Stations Vas. 2(2), 5(5), 7(1), 9(1), 12(2), 13(2), 14(2), 17(2), 18(1), 21(2), 24(2), 36(1), 39(1), 41(1).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9C8B6553FFC1BB572FA5284109E7FB2E" pageId="17" pageNumber="390" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="D42E36D8FFC1BB572FA5284109E7FB2E" blockId="17.[151,1437,1014,1438]" pageId="17" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis id="E6E5EACAFFC1BB572FA52841083BFBD7" bold="true" box="[151,305,1086,1112]" pageId="17" pageNumber="390">Distribution.</emphasis>
Mediterranean (
<bibRefCitation id="B0004B29FFC1BB572ED828400A3CFBD6" author="Bellan-Santini, D. &amp; Ruffo, S." box="[490,822,1087,1113]" pageId="17" pageNumber="390" pagination="273 - 292" refId="ref18519" refString="Bellan-Santini, D. &amp; Ruffo, S. (2003) Biogeography of benthic marine amphipods in Mediterranean Sea. Biogeographia-The Journal of Integrative Biogeography, 24 (1), 273 - 292. https: // doi. org / 10.21426 / B 6110176" type="journal article" year="2003">Bellan-Santini &amp; Ruffo 2003</bibRefCitation>
), Black Sea (WoRMS). The species was reported from 
<collectingCountry id="AC867648FFC1BB572FF4281C081DFBF2" box="[198,279,1123,1149]" name="Cyprus" pageId="17" pageNumber="390">Cyprus</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="B0004B29FFC1BB572E72281C0B26FBF2" author="Kocatas, A. &amp; Katagan, T." box="[320,556,1123,1149]" pageId="17" pageNumber="390" pagination="147 - 160" refId="ref20983" refString="Kocatas, A., Katagan, T. &amp; Huseyin. A. B. (2001) Contribution to the knowledge of the crustacean fauna of Cyprus. Israel Journal of Zoology, 47 (2), 147 - 160. https: // doi. org / 10.1560 / YQL 8 - 4 PBT- 12 W 2 - 82 HV" type="journal article" year="2001">
Kocatas 
<emphasis id="E6E5EACAFFC1BB572E92281C08D2FBF2" box="[416,472,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="390">et al.</emphasis>
(2001)
</bibRefCitation>
. In Vasiliko Bay (current study), it is considered as a common species (FI: 33.3 %).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9C8B6553FFC1BB572FA528D40B90FA11" pageId="17" pageNumber="390" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="D42E36D8FFC1BB572FA528D40B90FA11" blockId="17.[151,1437,1014,1438]" pageId="17" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis id="E6E5EACAFFC1BB572FA528D409F6FB4A" bold="true" box="[151,252,1195,1221]" pageId="17" pageNumber="390">Ecology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="13914D5BFFC1BB572E3728D40B0BFB4A" authorityName="Giordani-Soika" authorityYear="1950" box="[261,513,1195,1221]" class="Malacostraca" family="Calliopiidae" genus="Apherusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="17" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chiereghinii">
<emphasis id="E6E5EACAFFC1BB572E3728D40B0BFB4A" box="[261,513,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="390">Apherusa chiereghinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found in association with algae and on soft sediments (mud, mud and sand mixture) at 
<quantity id="13699B3DFFC1BB572E7828B108AAFB66" box="[330,416,1230,1257]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="390" unit="m" value="22.5" valueMax="45.0" valueMin="0.0">0–45 m</quantity>
depth (
<bibRefCitation id="B0004B29FFC1BB572EC728B00BD9FB66" author="Kocatas, A. &amp; Katagan, T." box="[501,723,1231,1257]" pageId="17" pageNumber="390" pagination="147 - 160" refId="ref20983" refString="Kocatas, A., Katagan, T. &amp; Huseyin. A. B. (2001) Contribution to the knowledge of the crustacean fauna of Cyprus. Israel Journal of Zoology, 47 (2), 147 - 160. https: // doi. org / 10.1560 / YQL 8 - 4 PBT- 12 W 2 - 82 HV" type="journal article" year="2001">Kocatas et al. 2001</bibRefCitation>
). In Vasiliko Bay it was found at 
<quantity id="13699B3DFFC1BB572B7F28B10DA9FB66" box="[1101,1187,1230,1257]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" metricValueMax="5.8" metricValueMin="0.4" pageId="17" pageNumber="390" unit="m" value="31.0" valueMax="58.0" valueMin="4.0">4–58 m</quantity>
depth (30 + 
<quantity id="13699B3DFFC1BB572A0728B00C78FB66" box="[1333,1394,1231,1257]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="17" pageNumber="390" unit="m" value="18.0">18 m</quantity>
), in sandy and muddy sand substrates with organic matter ranging between 2.2–6–11.119 % (5.543 + 2.826 %) and in association with 
<emphasis id="E6E5EACAFFC1BB572E9729680A61FABE" box="[421,875,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="390">
<taxonomicName id="13914D5BFFC1BB572E9729680B24FABE" authorityName="J. V. Lamouroux" authorityYear="1809" baseAuthorityName="Forsskal" box="[421,558,1303,1329]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Caulerpaceae" genus="Caulerpa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Bryopsidales" pageId="17" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="prolifera">C. prolifera</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="13914D5BFFC1BB572D0829680BEEFABE" authorityName="Sonder" authorityYear="1845" box="[570,740,1303,1329]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Caulerpaceae" genus="Caulerpa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Bryopsidales" pageId="17" pageNumber="390" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="cylindracea">C. cylindracea</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="13914D5BFFC1BB572DC329680A62FABE" authorityName="Ascherson" authorityYear="1870" baseAuthorityName="Ucria" box="[753,872,1303,1329]" class="Liliopsida" family="Cymodoceaceae" genus="Cymodocea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alismatales" pageId="17" pageNumber="390" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nodosa">C. nodosa</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="13914D5BFFC1BB572C4629680D02FABE" box="[884,1032,1303,1329]" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Dictyotaceae" genus="Dictyota" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dictyotales" pageId="17" pageNumber="377" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="spp">
<emphasis id="E6E5EACAFFC1BB572C4629680ADEFABF" box="[884,980,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="390">Dictyota</emphasis>
spp
</taxonomicName>
. and 
<taxonomicName id="13914D5BFFC1BB572B7429680DD7FABE" authorityName="Ascherson" authorityYear="1867" baseAuthorityName="Forsskal" box="[1094,1245,1303,1329]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Bugulidae" genus="Halophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="17" pageNumber="390" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="stipulacea">
<emphasis id="E6E5EACAFFC1BB572B7429680DD7FABE" box="[1094,1245,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="390">H. stipulacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It was found in stations classified according to the Bentix Index as in: “high” (2 stations, 4 individuals), “good” (7 stations, 14 individuals) and “moderate” (5 stations, 7 individuals). It was recorded at the power station outlet (2 individuals) and fish farm stations (8 individuals).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
